name: Emerica Brandon Westgate- Black/Dark Grey
description:
Brandon Westgate's new model for the holiday season.
The shoe is notable departure from the mid-rise vulcanized version that released some seasons ago, and this time takes cues from running-specific sneakers to produce an athletic, supportive silhouette. A key point here is the shoe’s lightness: the Brandon Westgate uses lightweight engineered mesh on the tongue and medial sidewall for superior breathability, while also cleverly cutting weight through cutouts in the outsole – which double to increase forefoot flexibility. The midsole is composed of high-rebound G6™ foam.

name: Tengu- God Of Mischief DVD
description:
Colin Read made a name for himself with his long running 'Mandible Claw' edits on the Slap Mag site for years. But during that whole time he was slowly crafting a long-form dvd project that was on a whole other level from his online work. After traveling filming for years and traveling across the US and the planet he wrapped up production and began premiering the video around the world, starting in NYC last month. Unsure of what to expect I went into the premiere assuming I would witness a long-form version of his Mandible Claw edits. But I was pleasantly surprised because Tengu proved itself to be a very solid piece of work that was very unique and offered a something new to the skate video world. Nowadays, with every skater being really skilled on the board, it's not hard to make a video with impressive skating. But to craft a video project that stands out as it's own unique work of art is a very difficult task indeed. And Colin has achieved this with Tengu. I recommend this video for any collector of underground, independent skate videos. You won't be disappointed.

Trailer-http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IHXpxkjO_J0

name: Eleventh Hour DVD
description:
A largely London based VX video, made over the period of a year, featuring Londoners and honoraries alike: parts from Nick Jensen, Luka Pinto, Tom Knox, Kevin Lowry, Sylvain Tognelli, Arthur Derrien, Daniel Clarke and Chris Jones – Peppered throughout with cameo appearances. Eleventh Hour is supported by Fourstar, Lakai, Isle Skateboards and Slam City Skates. Filmed and edited by Jacob Harris.

Trailer- http://vimeo.com/75018402

*This DVD is best viewed on a CRT Television.  It might not play in your standard DVD player, but will play on your CPU*
